cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.CV, cs.EM, cs.SY

The paper discusses a fully memristive spiking-neuron learning framework and its applications on pattern recognition and edge detection. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a neural network framework. 

cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of memristor devices, which are an emerging technology. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible category as the paper discusses the application of the framework on pattern recognition and edge detection. 

cs.EM (Electromagnetism) is a less likely category, but it is possible as the paper discusses the use of memristor models, which are related to electromagnetism. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a less likely category, but it is possible as the paper discusses the design of a neural network and cellular neural network, which are systems that can be controlled.
